## Datasets

The study employs a four-stage dataset development process:

| Stage | Records | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Base dataset | 300 | Six injectable products, 50 records each |
| Quality-enhanced | 498 | Monte Carlo simulation and parameter variation |
| Regional expansion | 1,992 | Four regions with region-specific environmental factors |
| Temporal expansion | 9,960 | Five-year period (2020–2024) with temporal factors |

**Products analyzed:** Botox 100U, Dysport 300U, Xeomin 100U, Restylane 1 mL, HA Filler 1 mL, Sculptra 5 mL.

**Regions covered:** European Union, United States, Turkey, Asia-Pacific.

**Functional unit:** One standard unit of injectable aesthetic product delivered to the point of clinical use.

## Requirements

The following Python packages are required:

```
pandas
numpy
matplotlib
seaborn
scikit-learn
shap
joblib
scipy
```

Install all dependencies:

```bash
pip install pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn scikit-learn shap joblib scipy
```

## Usage

**Train the model:**

```bash
cd AI_LCA_Complete_Codes/final_codes_package/codes/
python expanded_model_training.py
```

**Run SHAP analysis and hyperparameter tuning:**

```bash
cd AI_LCA_Complete_Codes/final_codes_package/codes/
python shap_residual_hyperparameter.py
```

**Run external validation (LORO-CV and Temporal Hold-Out):**

```bash
cd AI_LCA_Complete_Codes/final_codes_package/codes/
python external_validation.py
```

**Run uncertainty analysis (Bootstrap and Monte Carlo):**

```bash
cd AI_LCA_Complete_Codes/final_codes_package/codes/
python uncertainty_analysis.py
```

**Run statistical validation (KS tests, distribution comparison):**

```bash
cd AI_LCA_Complete_Codes/final_codes_package/codes/
python statistical_validation.py
```

**Run sensitivity analysis:**

```bash
cd AI_LCA_Complete_Codes/final_codes_package/codes/
python sensitivity_analysis.py
```

**Generate figures:**

```bash
cd AI_LCA_Complete_Codes/final_codes_package/graphics_codes/
python figure3_enhanced.py
python figure4_enhanced.py
python figure5_enhanced.py
python figure6_enhanced.py
python figure7_enhanced.py
python pasted_file_SQrZmP_figure8_enhanced.py
```

**Run model inference:**

```bash
cd AI_LCA_Complete_Codes/final_codes_package/codes/
python model_usage.py
```

## Model Performance

| Metric | Value |
| --- | --- |
| R² (test set) | 0.954 |
| RMSE | 0.132 kg CO₂e |
| MAE | 0.075 kg CO₂e |
| Algorithm | Random Forest Regressor |
| Number of trees | 250 |
| Maximum depth | 20 |
| Cross-validation R² (mean ± std) | 0.954 ± 0.018 |
| LORO-CV R² (mean) | 0.769 |
| Temporal Hold-Out R² (mean) | 0.992 |
| Bootstrap 95% CI relative uncertainty | 3.7–4.6% |

## Environmental Impact Results

| Product | Carbon Footprint (kg CO₂e) | Cold Chain |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Botox 100U | 1.600 | Yes |
| Dysport 300U | 1.494 | Yes |
| Xeomin 100U | 0.349 | No |
| Restylane 1 mL | 0.176 | No |
| HA Filler 1 mL | 0.151 | No |
| Sculptra 5 mL | 0.111 | No |

## Validation Framework

The model was validated using a comprehensive multi-level approach:

1. **5-Fold Cross-Validation:** Mean R² = 0.954 (std = 0.018), confirming prediction stability.

1. **Leave-One-Region-Out CV (LORO-CV):** Mean R² = 0.769, assessing geographic generalizability.

1. **Temporal Hold-Out Validation:** Mean R² = 0.992, confirming temporal generalizability.

1. **Bootstrap Uncertainty Analysis:** 10,000 iterations, 95% CI relative uncertainty 3.7–4.6%.

1. **Monte Carlo Propagation:** 10,000 simulations, 95% CI relative uncertainty 77–79%.

1. **Statistical Validation:** Kolmogorov-Smirnov tests, t-tests, and CV analysis at each expansion stage.

